0 0 0
E
move~
#C How to Move#n

write page title #0Going to mobs#n
wr start.action.spell
wr victim.target
wr global.target
wr move
wr message.1:   You step into a rift of energy.
wr message.2: $n steps into a rift of energy.
wr message.3: $n steps out of a rift of energy.
wr end.spell

Okay, alot can be done with these.   You can make it to
objects by making it object.target, and you can  add a reversed
line to summon mobs/objects. These, like anything else, can be chained,
so you can chain summon if you learn about 'parameters'. You
can also use 'action' spells to create mobs and objects, but they
But the objects cannot be used on quests.  These are advanced lessons
that I urge you to find someone of wisdom to teach.  Mortimer is
skilled at these and has a Tome with many for you to peruse.
~
E
bless~
#CBasics of a Bless#n


write page title #0Bless#n
wr start.affect.spell
wr victim.target
wr global.target
wr apply: hp
wr apply: mana
wr apply: move
wr apply: hit
wr apply: dam
wr apply: ac
wr apply: save
wr bonus: 100
wr duration: 55
wr message.1: You have blessed $N.
wr message.2: You have been blessed.
wr message.3: You have been blessed.
wr next.page
wr end.spell

Now, it's time to explain a few things. apply: adds things like stats.
If you want, you can add str, dex, con, etc, but that is solely up
to you. Bonus is how much it adds to the chosen applied stats, and
duration is how many mud hours it lasts. Max Duration is 60,
max bonus is 100.
~
E
train~
#CBasics of a Train#n


write page title #0Train#n
wr start.affect.spell
wr victim.target
wr global.target
wr reversed
wr apply: hp
wr apply: mana
wr apply: move
wr bonus: 100
wr duration: 55
wr message.1: You have trained $N.
wr message.2: You have been trained.
wr message.3: You have been trained.
wr next.page
wr end.spell

Okay, Blesses and trains can all have the same things on them.
But, trains lower stats as opposed to raised.  This is performed
by the 'reversed' line in the spell.  Keep in mind, that should you
want to experiment with 'Combat trains', you can add hit, dam, ac,
and maybe even affects. These are in the next lesson. Proceed, please.
~
E
desanct~
#CDesanct#n


write page title #0Desanct#n
wr start.affect.spell
wr victim.target
wr global.target
wr affect: sanct
wr affect: protection
wr message.1: You lower your defences.
wr message.2: You lower your defences.
wr message.3: You lower your defences.
wr end.spell

Now, notice a few things. There are no duration/bonus, as you
don't want them. As soon as this page wears off the target,
they lose the affects that are on this bomb.  So naturally,
they'll lose sanct and protection.  Use this to your advantage.
You don't want them to know you're doing it, so make the message
discreet, if not non-existant.  You can use these types of pages
in your bombs, on the end, the 15th page.  Instead of sanct/protect,
make affect: for flaming, curse, web, poison, and faerie.fire.
These will prove useful to you.  Next lesson, please.
~
